 personal and national identities. Focusing on both the experience of military service and its imaginative forms, it examines such topics as bodies and habits, families and domesticity, heroism and chivalry, religion and militarism, and youth and fantasy. This collection will be required reading for anyone interested in the cultures of war and masculinity in the long nineteenth century.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGreat Britain-Social conditions-19th century. 0aMasculinityzGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aMasculinity-Great Britain-History-19th century. 0aSociology, MilitaryzGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aSociology, Military-Great Britain-History-19th century. 7aHISTORY / Military / General.2bisacsh  aGreat Britain.  achivalry.  aculture and society.  afantasy.  aheroism.  amasculinity.  amilitarism.  apersonal habits.  areligion.1 aBanister, Julia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarry, Anna Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarry, Anna Maria, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBegiato, Joanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBegiato, Joanne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBrown, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrown, Michael, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCarter, Louise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoodman, Helen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLand, Isaac, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeonardi, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCausland, Elly, econtributor.4ctb4